    "rationale": "This example demonstrates the selective reduction of a ketone (alpha-tetralone) to a methylene group (tetralin) under Wolff-Kishner conditions. The aromatic ring is stable to these conditions, highlighting the chemoselectivity of the reaction for the carbonyl group. The fused ring system provides a clear, non-trivial substrate that is a classic textbook example of this transformation.",
    "collision_avoidance_note": "The substrate is alpha-tetralone, a fused bicyclic ketone, which is structurally distinct from simple acyclic or monocyclic ketones like acetophenone or cyclohexanone. This avoids trivial examples and potential overlap with generic carbonyl reduction seeds.",
